traffic_visible_response: "Second Yuan" could refer to the second series of the Chinese currency Renminbi (RMB) issued by the People's Bank of China on March 1, 1955[^1^]. This series of RMB was introduced to replace the first series due to issues such as large face values and poor paper quality[^2^]. The second series included a 2 yuan note, which featured the Bao塔Mountain on the front and had main colors of dark blue, earth yellow, and gray-blue[^1^]. This 2 yuan note circulated until it was gradually phased out, with the fourth series of RMB's 2 yuan note being officially demonetized on May 1, 2018[^1^].
